 discoveries and treatments for Meibomian gland dysfunction (MGD), an underlying disease that leads to Dry Eye syndrome and involves blockage of the oil-producing tear glands within the eyelids. Not only are these glands key to clear vision and comfortable eyes, but when disrupted they can cause severe pain and a host of related symptoms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aDry eye syndromesxTreatment. 0aDry eye syndromes. 7aMEDICAL / Ophthalmology.2bisacsh1 aWarren, Natalia A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300264982?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300264982423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300264982/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles